---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Home" description="Comprehensive guide to fertility treatments in the US. Compare IVF, IUI, medications, and more with costs, success rates, and decision-making tools.">
	<section class="hero">
		<div class="container">
			<h1>Understanding Your Fertility Treatment Options</h1>
			<p class="lead">A comprehensive guide to fertility treatments in the United States, including costs, success rates, and decision-making tools to help you navigate your journey.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="content-container">
		<h2>Getting Started</h2>
		<p>Navigating fertility treatments can feel overwhelming. This guide is designed to help you understand your options, compare costs, and make informed decisions alongside your healthcare team.</p>

		<div class="info-box">
			<strong>Before You Begin:</strong> Fertility treatment recommendations depend on your specific diagnosis, age, medical history, and personal preferences. Always work with a reproductive endocrinologist (RE) to develop a personalized treatment plan.
		</div>

		<h2>Who is Affected?</h2>
		<p>Infertility affects approximately <strong>1 in 6 couples</strong> trying to conceive. Contrary to common perception, infertility is not primarily a female issue—causes are distributed relatively equally between partners.</p>

		<div class="card stats-card">
			<h3>Distribution of Infertility Causes</h3>
			<table>
				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>Attribution</th>
						<th>Percentage</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td>Female factors only</td>
						<td>~35%</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Male factors only</td>
						<td>~35%</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Combined male and female factors</td>
						<td>~20%</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Unexplained (no identifiable cause)</td>
						<td>~10-25%</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>
			<p class="citation">Source: <a href="https://www.reproductivefacts.org/browse-resources/frequently-asked-questions/faq-about-infertility/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ASRM ReproductiveFacts.org</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK556033/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NCBI StatPearls</a></p>
		</div>

		<h2>Most Common Causes</h2>
		<div class="causes-grid">
			<div class="card">
				<h3>Ovulatory Disorders</h3>
				<p class="stat">25% of female infertility</p>
				<p>Problems with ovulation, most commonly caused by PCOS, which affects 5-20% of women of reproductive age and accounts for 70-80% of anovulatory infertility.</p>
				<p class="citation">Source: <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK459251/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NCBI StatPearls</a></p>
			</div>

			<div class="card">
				<h3>Tubal Factor</h3>
				<p class="stat">20-35% of female infertility</p>
				<p>Blocked or damaged fallopian tubes, often caused by pelvic inflammatory disease, endometriosis, or prior surgery.</p>
				<p class="citation">Source: <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK556033/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NCBI StatPearls</a></p>
			</div>

			<div class="card">
				<h3>Endometriosis</h3>
				<p class="stat">25-50% of infertile women</p>
				<p>Tissue similar to the uterine lining grows outside the uterus. Women with endometriosis are 6-8 times more likely to experience infertility.</p>
				<p class="citation">Source: <a href="https://www.asrm.org/practice-guidance/practice-committee-documents/endometriosis-and-infertility-a-committee-opinion-2012/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ASRM Committee Opinion</a></p>
			</div>

			<div class="card">
				<h3>Male Factor</h3>
				<p class="stat">~40% involve male factors</p>
				<p>Varicocele is the most common cause (~40% of infertile men). Other causes include low sperm count, poor motility, and hormonal disorders.</p>
				<p class="citation">Source: <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK562258/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NCBI StatPearls</a></p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<p><a href="/causes/">View detailed causes and statistics →</a></p>

		<h2>Treatment Options</h2>
		<div class="treatment-grid">
			<div class="card">
				<h3>Lifestyle & Medication</h3>
				<p>Often the first step. Includes ovulation induction with oral medications like Clomid or Letrozole.</p>
				<p><strong>Typical cost:</strong> $100 - $1,500/cycle</p>
				<p><a href="/treatments/medication/">Learn more</a></p>
			</div>

			<div class="card">
				<h3>IUI (Intrauterine Insemination)</h3>
				<p>A less invasive procedure where prepared sperm is placed directly in the uterus during ovulation.</p>
				<p><strong>Typical cost:</strong> $500 - $4,000/cycle</p>
				<p><a href="/treatments/iui/">Learn more</a></p>
			</div>

			<div class="card">
				<h3>IVF (In Vitro Fertilization)</h3>
				<p>Eggs are retrieved, fertilized in a lab, and embryos are transferred to the uterus.</p>
				<p><strong>Typical cost:</strong> $12,000 - $25,000/cycle</p>
				<p><a href="/treatments/ivf/">Learn more</a></p>
			</div>

			<div class="card">
				<h3>Third-Party Reproduction</h3>
				<p>Includes donor eggs, donor sperm, donor embryos, and gestational surrogacy.</p>
				<p><strong>Typical cost:</strong> $5,000 - $150,000+</p>
				<p><a href="/treatments/third-party/">Learn more</a></p>
			</div>

			<div class="card">
				<h3>Fertility Preservation</h3>
				<p>Egg freezing or sperm freezing for future use, often before medical treatment or for elective reasons.</p>
				<p><strong>Typical cost:</strong> $5,000 - $15,000 + storage</p>
				<p><a href="/treatments/preservation/">Learn more</a></p>
			</div>

			<div class="card">
				<h3>Surgical Options</h3>
				<p>Procedures to address structural issues like fibroids, endometriosis, or blocked fallopian tubes.</p>
				<p><strong>Typical cost:</strong> $5,000 - $30,000</p>
				<p><a href="/treatments/surgical/">Learn more</a></p>
			</div>

			<div class="card">
				<h3>Recurrent Pregnancy Loss</h3>
				<p>Specialized testing and treatment after 2+ consecutive miscarriages.</p>
				<p><strong>Typical cost:</strong> $2,000 - $35,000</p>
				<p><a href="/treatments/recurrent-loss/">Learn more</a></p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<h2>Quick Links</h2>
		<ul>
			<li><a href="/causes/">Causes of Infertility</a> - Statistics and research on what causes infertility</li>
			<li><a href="/costs/">Full Cost Comparison</a> - Detailed breakdown of treatment costs</li>
			<li><a href="/decision-guide/">Decision Guide</a> - Interactive flowcharts to help you understand your options</li>
			<li><a href="/resources/">Resources</a> - Insurance, financial assistance, and support organizations</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Key Factors in Treatment Decisions</h2>
		<table>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th>Factor</th>
					<th>Why It Matters</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<td>Age</td>
					<td>Egg quality and quantity decline with age, affecting success rates and treatment recommendations</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Diagnosis</td>
					<td>The underlying cause of infertility guides which treatments are most likely to succeed</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Duration of Infertility</td>
					<td>Longer duration may indicate need for more advanced treatments</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Previous Treatments</td>
					<td>Response to prior treatments helps predict success of future options</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Financial Resources</td>
					<td>Out-of-pocket costs vary significantly; insurance coverage affects treatment access</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Personal Values</td>
					<td>Religious, ethical, and personal preferences influence treatment choices</td>
				</tr>
			</tbody>
		</table>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.hero {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2c5282 0%, #1a365d 100%);
		color: white;
		padding: 4rem 0;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.hero h1 {
		color: white;
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
		font-size: 2.5rem;
	}

	.lead {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		max-width: 700px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		opacity: 0.95;
	}

	.stats-card {
		background: #f0fff4;
		border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
	}

	.causes-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
		gap: 1.5rem;
		margin: 2rem 0;
	}

	.causes-grid .card {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.causes-grid .stat {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--color-primary);
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
	}

	.causes-grid .citation {
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		color: var(--color-text-light);
		margin-top: 0.75rem;
		padding-top: 0.5rem;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.treatment-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
		gap: 1.5rem;
		margin: 2rem 0;
	}

	.treatment-grid .card {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.treatment-grid .card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.hero {
			padding: 3rem 0;
		}

		.hero h1 {
			font-size: 1.875rem;
		}

		.lead {
			font-size: 1.125rem;
		}
	}
</style>
